The Original Turtle Trading Rules Strategy 2020-06-20 original implementation - FengkieJ 2020-06-27 rev 1. add System 1 & System 2 as strategy parameters - FengkieJ

Turtle strategy is one of classic trend-following system that has clear defined trading rules. The system was taught by Richard Dennis and William Eckhardt in 1983. This version implements the system described by Curtis Faith, author of bestselling book Way of the Turtle.

This Python module attempts to implement the system on backtrader framework as described in the pdf by Curtis Faith & Perry J. Kaufman.

This module is designed for Turtle Trading Strategy¶

  1. Entry condition: When the product price surpasses the highest point within the last 20 days (Price at T+1 opening).
  2. Exit condition: When the product price falls below the lowest point within the last 10 days (Price at T closing).
  3. Risk for any given trade should not exceed 2% of the account's net assets.
  4. Increase position by 1/2 ATR of the corresponding product (position size can be self-adjusted).

The following recommendations will enhance this module:¶

- Refine profit related ratio like cumulative daily returns;
- Utilize an indicator to display trade directions and corresponding numbers;

In Financial View

class TurtleStrategy(bt.Strategy):
    params = (('long_period',20),
              ('short_period',10),  
              ('printlog', False), ) 
    
    def __init__(self):        
        self.order = None      
        self.buyprice = 0      
        self.buycomm = 0      
        self.buy_size = 0      
        self.buy_count = 0
        
        # Donchian and ATR     
        self.H_line = bt.indicators.Highest(self.data.high(-1), period=self.p.long_period)        
        self.L_line = bt.indicators.Lowest(self.data.low(-1), period=self.p.short_period) 
        self.M_line = (self.H_line+self.L_line)/2
        self.TR = bt.indicators.TrueRange(self.data)      
        self.ATR = bt.indicators.SimpleMovingAverage(self.TR,period=self.p.long_period)       
        # Signal      
        self.buy_signal = bt.ind.CrossOver(self.data.close(0), self.H_line)        
        self.sell_signal = bt.ind.CrossOver(self.data.close(0), self.L_line)
        
    def next(self): 
        if self.order:
            return
        
        # Entry condition       
        if self.buy_signal > 0 and self.buy_count == 0:                                 
            self.buy_size = self.broker.getvalue() * 0.01 / self.ATR            
            self.buy_size  = int(self.buy_size / 100) * 100                             
            self.sizer.p.stake = self.buy_size             
            self.buy_count = 1            
            self.order = self.buy()
            
        # Exit condition    
        elif self.sell_signal < 0 and self.buy_count > 0:            
            self.order = self.sell()            
            self.buy_count = 0 

        # Increase position by 1/2 ATR of the corresponding product & No more than 4 times      
        elif self.data.close >self.buyprice+0.5*self.ATR[0] and self.buy_count > 0 and self.buy_count <=4:           
            self.buy_size  = self.broker.getvalue() * 0.01 / self.ATR            
            self.buy_size  = int(self.buy_size  / 100) * 100            
            self.sizer.p.stake = self.buy_size             
            self.order = self.buy()           
            self.buy_count += 1        
         
        # Risk Management
        size = (self.broker.getvalue() * 0.01) / self.ATR[0]
        total_risk = size * self.ATR[0]

        # Do not risk more than 2% of account equity on a single trade.
        if total_risk > (self.broker.getvalue() * 0.02):
            return

                  
    # Order Log
    def log(self, txt, dt=None,doprint=False):
        if self.params.printlog or doprint:
            dt = dt or self.datas[0].datetime.date(0)
            print(f'{dt.isoformat()},{txt}')
            
    # Order Status
    def notify_order(self, order):
        if order.status in [order.Submitted, order.Accepted]:
            return
        if order.status in [order.Completed]: 
            if order.isbuy():
                self.log(f'BUY EXECUTED\nPrice At:{order.executed.price},\
                Cost:{order.executed.value},\
                Commission:{order.executed.comm}')
                self.buyprice = order.executed.price
                self.buycomm = order.executed.comm
            else:
                self.log(f'SELL EXECUTED\nPrice At：{order.executed.price},\
                Cost: {order.executed.value},\
                Commission:{order.executed.comm}')
            self.bar_executed = len(self) 
        # IF cancel/ reject order
        elif order.status in [order.Canceled, order.Margin, order.Rejected]:
            self.log('Order Canceled/Margin/Rejected')
        self.order = None
        
    # Trade
    def notify_trade(self,trade):
        if not trade.isclosed:
            return
            
        self.log(f'Strategy Return：\nGross Profit {trade.pnl:.2f}, Net Profit {trade.pnlcomm:.2f}')
        
    def stop(self):
        self.log(f'(Period：{self.p.long_period},{self.p.short_period})； \
        Final Portfolio Value: {self.broker.getvalue():.2f}', doprint=False)

This module is designed for backtesting based on yahoo finance.¶

AUDNZD TICKER : AUDNZD=X

With conditions:
1.Test Portfolio (Products): AUDNZD 2.Trading Commission: 0.0002% of the transaction amount
3.Test Duration: July 1, 2020, to July 1, 2023
4.Initial Test Capital: $1,000,000 USD

def run_backtest():
    cerebro = bt.Cerebro()

    data = yf.download("AUDNZD=X",'2020-07-01','2023-07-01')
    datafeed = bt.feeds.PandasData(dataname=data)
    cerebro.adddata(datafeed)

    cerebro.addstrategy(TurtleStrategy)
    cerebro.broker.setcash(1000000.0)
    cerebro.broker.setcommission(commission=0.000002)

    print('Starting Portfolio Value: %.2f' % cerebro.broker.getvalue())
    cerebro.addanalyzer(bt.analyzers.PyFolio, _name='PyFolio')
    results = cerebro.run()
    strat = results[0]
    print('Final Portfolio Value: %.2f' % cerebro.broker.getvalue())
    cerebro.plot()
